====================
JENKINS PIPELINE 
====================

--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS JENKINS PIPELINE?
--------------------------------------------------

    Jenkins Pipeline is a way to define CI/CD
    process as CODE.

    Instead of manual UI steps (freestyle),
    we write pipeline in a file called:

        Jenkinsfile

    It automates:

        • Build
        • Test
        • Deploy


--------------------------------------------------
WHY PIPELINE IS REQUIRED?
--------------------------------------------------

    Problems with Freestyle Jobs:

        • Manual configuration
        • Hard to track changes
        • Not reusable
        • Difficult for complex workflows
		. UI based 

    Pipeline solves:

        • Code-based configuration - Pipeline as Code
        • Version control (Git)
        • Easy automation
        • Supports complex workflows
        • Reusable
        • Supports parallel execution
        • Better visibility
        • Easy automation
        • Supports CI/CD fully
       

--------------------------------------------------
WHAT IS JENKINSFILE?
--------------------------------------------------

    A file that contains pipeline code.

    Stored in project repo (GitHub).

Example:

    pipeline {
        agent any

        stages {
            stage('Build') {
                steps {
                    echo "Build started"
                }
            }
        }
    }


--------------------------------------------------
PIPELINE STAGES
--------------------------------------------------

    Typical stages:

        • Checkout
        • Build
        • Test
        • Package
        • Deploy



--------------------------------------------------
TYPES OF PIPELINES
--------------------------------------------------

    1) Declarative Pipeline
    2) Scripted Pipeline


--------------------------------------------------
1) DECLARATIVE PIPELINE
--------------------------------------------------

    Simple and structured syntax.

    Uses predefined blocks:

        pipeline { }
        stages { }
        steps { }

Example:

    pipeline {
        agent any

        stages {
            stage('Build') {
                steps {
                    echo "Building app"
                }
            }

            stage('Test') {
                steps {
                    echo "Testing app"
                }
            }
        }
    }



--------------------------------------------------
2) SCRIPTED PIPELINE
--------------------------------------------------


    node {
        stage('Build') {
            echo "Building app"
        }

        stage('Test') {
            echo "Testing app"
        }
    }

Features:

    • Full programming control
    • Complex logic possible
    • Harder to understand



--------------------------------------------------
REAL DEVOPS USE CASE
--------------------------------------------------

    Developer pushes code → GitHub

        ↓

    Jenkins triggers pipeline

        ↓

    Build using Maven

        ↓

    Run tests

        ↓

    Build Docker image

        ↓

    Deploy to Kubernetes






